'''Shōheizaka Academy''' (昌平坂学問所):
The {{ill|Shōheizaka Academy|ja|昌平坂学問所|12=draft|12=draft}} was an educational and research institution directly managed by the {{ill|Tokugawa Shogunate|ja|Tokugawa shogunate|12=draft|12=draft}}. Established in {{ill|1790|ja|1790th year|12=draft|12=draft}} (Kansei 2) in {{ill|Yushima|ja|湯島|12=draft|12=draft}}, Kanda, it served as a centralized location for Confucian studies. Its formal designation was "Gakumonjo" (学問所), but it was also referred to as "Shōheikō" (昌平黌).
== History == [[File:Yushima Seido6.jpg|thumb|The "Taiseiden" (Confucius Shrine) at Yushima Seido (February 3, 2010)]] {{See also|Yushima Seido}} === As the Hayashi Family's Private Academy === In {{ill|1605|ja|1605th year|12=draft|12=draft}} (Keichō 10), {{ill|Hayashi Razan|ja|林羅山|12=draft|12=draft}} entered the service of Tokugawa Ieyasu as a Buddhist scholar. By {{ill|1630|ja|1630th year|12=draft|12=draft}} (Kan'ei 7), Tokugawa Iemitsu granted the Hayashi family land in Ueno for a school. This was the foundation of what would later become the Shōheizaka Academy.
=== Establishment of the Gakumonjo === In {{ill|1790|ja|1790th year|12=draft|12=draft}} (Kansei 2), as part of the "Kansei Edict on Neo-Confucianism" (寛政異学の禁), the institution was reorganized into a government-operated academy.
=== Transition to "Shōhei School" === During the Meiji Restoration, the academy was briefly rebranded as the "Shōhei School" but was eventually dissolved in {{ill|1870|ja|1870th year|12=draft|12=draft}} (Meiji 3). It had limited influence on the formation of the modern {{ill|University of Tokyo|ja|東京大学|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Related Literature == * {{Cite book|和書 |title=昌平坂学問所日記 |volume=1 |editor=斯文会・橋本昭彦 |publisher=斯文会・東洋書院（発売） |date=1998-12 |isbn=9784885942785}} * {{Cite book|和書 |title=昌平坂学問所日記 |volume=2 |editor=斯文会・橋本昭彦 |publisher=斯文会・東洋書院（発売） |date=2002-03 |isbn=9784885943188}} == See Also == * {{ill|Confucian Scholars|ja|1=Ru (Confucian scholar)|儒学者|zh|儒生|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Hayashi Razan|ja|林羅山|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Kansei Edict on Neo-Confucianism|ja|寛政異学の禁|12=draft|12=draft}}
