=== Transition to "Shōhei School" === During the Meiji Restoration, the academy was briefly rebranded as the "Shōhei School" but was eventually dissolved in {{ill|1870|ja|1870th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Meiji 3). It had limited influence on the formation of the modern {{ill|University of Tokyo|ja|東京大学|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
