== History == [[File:Yushima Seido6.jpg|thumb|The "Taiseiden" (Confucius Shrine) at Yushima Seido (February 3, 2010)]] {{See also|Yushima Seido}} === As the Hayashi Family's Private Academy === In [[:en:1605|1605]] (Keichō 10), [[:en:Hayashi Razan|Hayashi Razan]] entered the service of Tokugawa Ieyasu as a Buddhist scholar. By [[:en:1630|1630]] (Kan'ei 7), Tokugawa Iemitsu granted the Hayashi family land in Ueno for a school. This was the foundation of what would later become the Shōheizaka Academy.
=== Establishment of the Gakumonjo === In [[:en:1790|1790]] (Kansei 2), as part of the "Kansei Edict on Neo-Confucianism" (寛政異学の禁), the institution was reorganized into a government-operated academy.
=== Transition to "Shōhei School" === During the Meiji Restoration, the academy was briefly rebranded as the "Shōhei School" but was eventually dissolved in [[:en:1870|1870]] (Meiji 3). It had limited influence on the formation of the modern [[:en:University of Tokyo|University of Tokyo]].
