{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q4059219]] Wikidata name: Shōheizaka Gakumonjo [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 09:28, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} '''Shōheizaka Academy''' (昌平坂学問所):
The {{ill|Shōheizaka Academy|ja|昌平坂学問所|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōheizaka Academy|qq=|1=Shōheizaka Gakumonjo|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q4059219}} was an educational and research institution directly managed by the {{ill|Tokugawa shogunate|1=Tokugawa shogunate|2=ja|3=江戸幕府|lt=Tokugawa shogunate|lt=Tokugawa Shogunate|ja|Tokugawa shogunate|1=Tokugawa shogunate|2=ja|3=江戸幕府|lt=Tokugawa shogunate|lt=Tokugawa Shogunate|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokugawa Shogunate|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. Established in [[:en:1790|1790]] (Kansei 2) in {{ill|Yushima|ja|湯島|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yushima|qq=|1=Yushima|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11563516}}, Kanda, it served as a centralized location for Confucian studies. Its formal designation was "Gakumonjo" (学問所), but it was also referred to as "Shōheikō" (昌平黌).
== History == [[File:Yushima Seido6.jpg|thumb|The "Taiseiden" (Confucius Shrine) at Yushima Seido (February 3, 2010)]] {{See also|Yushima Seido}} === As the Hayashi Family's Private Academy === In [[:en:1605|1605]] (Keichō 10), [[:en:Hayashi Razan|Hayashi Razan]] entered the service of Tokugawa Ieyasu as a Buddhist scholar. By [[:en:1630|1630]] (Kan'ei 7), Tokugawa Iemitsu granted the Hayashi family land in Ueno for a school. This was the foundation of what would later become the Shōheizaka Academy.
=== Establishment of the Gakumonjo === In [[:en:1790|1790]] (Kansei 2), as part of the "Kansei Edict on Neo-Confucianism" (寛政異学の禁), the institution was reorganized into a government-operated academy.
=== Transition to "Shōhei School" === During the Meiji Restoration, the academy was briefly rebranded as the "Shōhei School" but was eventually dissolved in [[:en:1870|1870]] (Meiji 3). It had limited influence on the formation of the modern [[:en:University of Tokyo|University of Tokyo]].
== Related Literature == * {{Cite book|和書 |title=昌平坂学問所日記 |volume=1 |editor=斯文会・橋本昭彦 |publisher=斯文会・東洋書院（発売） |date=1998-12 |isbn=9784885942785}} * {{Cite book|和書 |title=昌平坂学問所日記 |volume=2 |editor=斯文会・橋本昭彦 |publisher=斯文会・東洋書院（発売） |date=2002-03 |isbn=9784885943188}} == See Also == * {{ill|Confucian Scholars|ja|1=Ru (Confucian scholar)|儒学者|zh|儒生|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Confucian Scholars|13=User:Immanuelle/Ru (Confucian scholar)|qq=}} * [[:en:Hayashi Razan|Hayashi Razan]] * {{ill|Kansei Edict on Neo-Confucianism|ja|寛政異学の禁|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kansei Edict on Neo-Confucianism|qq=|comment=changed title based on wikidata|1=Kansei Edict|WD=Q3579139}}
